ses taken in the major  exclusive of subjects taken in the 4th Class year  and have permission of the department head  Cadets must complete ML 498 and ML 499 and produce a thesis which is written in the student s major foreign language  as appropriate  The thesis must achieve a language ranking of  Advanced High  and adhere to MLA specifications    VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 